  "original_title": "\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dda\u0dc1\u0dd3\u0dba \u0daf\u0dd4\u0db8\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da7\u0dd2 \u0dc3\u0dc4 \u0db8\u0dad\u0dca\u0db4\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc3\u0db8\u0d9c 02\u0d9a\u0dca \u0db8\u0dcf\u0da7\u0dca\u0da7\u0dd4",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "02 caught with foreign cigarettes and alcohol",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Two persons were arrested by the Special Task Force officers along with a stock of foreign cigarettes, liquor and dried turmeric worth more than one crore rupees that were illegally imported into Sri Lanka.",
        "Two persons aged 32 and 44, residents of Pussellawa and Kotmale, have been arrested.",
        "According to the information received by the officers of Organized Crime Unit 11 of the Special Task Force, a team of officers including Inspector P.W.A.J.P.K.Wanniarachchi conducted a three-wheeler raid near the Kiribathgoda fuel station as per the instructions of the Special Task Force Commander DIG Varuna Jayasundara. The two suspects were arrested along with a stock of illegally imported foreign cigarettes that were being transported in a vehicle and during further questioning, a stock of illegally imported foreign liquor and dried turmeric hidden in a house located on Wevelduwa Road, Wattala, Hunupitiya was arrested.",
        "During this raid, 40000 foreign cigarettes, 720 bottles of foreign liquor, 4700 kg of dry turmeric and the three-wheeler used to transport them were arrested.",
        "The arrested suspects have been handed over to the Kiribathgoda police to be produced in court."
      ],
